result.execSummary:
The defendant Darrell W Cunningham was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Court ordered Fine of $250.00 plus of all applicable costs, fees and surcharges to be paid by 07-05-2016 .  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank - surcharge IMPOSED.

Court will consider motion for expungement if defendant pays the fine  within 30 days of todays date.

Defendant Darrell W Cunningham in court with attorney Steven Rees Wiechmann.  Danielle Chojnacki appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: sm
Case set for plea and sentencing hearing.  State placed Negotiations on the record. 

Parties proceeds to  plea hearing.
Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. 

Case proceeds to sentencing in Branch 22.
